interview.name: start
interview.label: How would you characterize your experience as an interviewer/interviewee?

interview.name: purposes
interview.label: What are some of the purposes of the interviews you've been involved in? (data gathering, recruiting, health diagnostics, investigative journalism)

interview.name: duration
interview.label: How long do your interviews usually last? Did you usually have an idea of how far along you are in the interview?

interview.name: sittings
interview.label: Have you participated in interviews that took place over multiple sittings? Does this seem to be a common case?

interview.name: medium
interview.label: Have your interviews been in person? on the phone? written response?

interview.name: admin
interview.label: Have you been involved in any interviewing projects in an administrative capacity? What tasks did you perform?

children.name: challenges
children.label: Which tasks do you find the most challenging or time consuming?

children.name: experience
children.label: What level of training or experience is typically required in your interviews?

children.name: branching
children.label: Have you administered any interviews with branching logic?

children.name: follow-ups
children.label:
Do you tend to ask follow-up questions beyond what is suggested in the survey?
How/when do they usually occur? How are they dealt with in coding?

children.name: recording
children.label:
Are your interviews recorded?
Have you encountered any limitations in being allowed to record?

children.name: notes
children.label: Do you take notes during your interviews?

children.name: contingencies
children.label: Have you ever needed to discard recordings/notes that you collected?

interview.name: comments
interview.label: Do you have any comments about the tool I am using? About the interview experience as a whole?
